      "content": "that makes sense, but some people argue that systemic factors don't fully explain the numbers, especially when you look at crime rates in certain neighborhoods. if you look at the actual data trends, do you think there's a cultural or behavioral aspect to why some groups end up in the system more often, or is it strictly just about the socioeconomic stuff you mentioned?",
